Combine the @teriyaki marinade paste{50%g} and the @diced chicken breast{260%g} in a #mixing bowl{}. Mix together well with your hands to coat the chicken, then set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat!

Trim the @green beans{150%g} and chop into thirds. Trim the root from @spring onion{2} then finely slice. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Peel and grate the @ginger{1%piece}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. Add the chicken and its marinade and stir-fry for ~{4%minutes}. Add the green beans and stir-fry for another ~{4-5%minutes}.

In another large frying pan heat a drizzle of oil over high heat. Once hot, add the garlic, ginger and half the spring onion. Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{2%minutes}. Squeeze the @steamed basmati rice{1%portion} pouch, open the packet then tip the rice into the pan. Stir-fry for another ~{2-3%minutes} until the rice is piping hot.

Lower the heat to medium, pour the @water{100%ml} into the pan stir, then bubble gently for ~{2-3%minutes} until thickened slightly.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Toss half the @sesame seeds{15%g} through the chicken. Serve the ginger rice in #bowls{} topped with the sesame chicken. Finish with a sprinkling of remaining sesame seeds and spring onion. ENJOY!